article.headline: Youngstown State 95, Slippery Rock 53
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Keston Roberts scored 27 points and Derrick Harris passed for 13 assists to help Youngstown State beat Slippery Rock 95-53 on Wednesday. The Penguins (1-1) opened the game with a 10-2 run and never trailed. They led by as many as 43 in the second half. Quin Humphrey had 18 points and nine rebounds for Youngstown State, which outrebounded Slippery Rock 48-25 and forced 20 turnovers. Domonique Crawford also scored 18 points and John Barber added 11. Nathanael McCoy scored 11 points for NCAA Division II Slippery Rock (1-2). Humprey made a 3-pointer with 6:23 left in the first half to spark a 20-2 run that gave Youngstown State a 52-26 lead. Roberts had nine points in the spurt. The Penguins shot 49 percent from the field, including 11-for-30 from 3-point range. Dejan Jancic also had 10 points for Slippery Rock.
